---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../config";
---

<PageLayout content={{ title: "About | Giwan Persaud", description: "Learn more about Giwan, a senior frontend developer and creator behind this editorial blog." }}>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
        <header class="text-center mb-16 border-b border-border pb-12">
            <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-muted-foreground mb-4 block italic">Behind the Publication</span>
            <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-6">
                Hi, I'm Giwan.
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl font-serif italic text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Senior frontend developer by day, creator of digital experiments by night.
                Building with intention, one side project at a time.
            </p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-2xl prose-serif max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
            <p>
                I'm a senior frontend developer who likes to build. 
                This is just one of the side projects I spend time on. 
                My primary side project is <a href="https://mytoori.com" target="_blank" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4">Mytoori.com</a>.
            </p>

            <p>
                I grew up speaking both English at home and Dutch at school. Later, I traveled quite a bit for work, picking up a few other languages along the way. German is close enough to Dutch so I cheat a bit there; I spent a year living in France but lost some fluency when I left. I'm currently learning and struggling with Portuguese.
            </p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 my-16 border-y border-border py-12 not-prose">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-foreground">The Stack</h3>
                    <p class="font-serif text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                        I mostly develop with <a href="https://react.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">ReactJS</a> but
                        have dabbled with <a href="https://svelte.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">SvelteKit</a> and <a href="https://vuejs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">VueJS</a>.
                        Meta frameworks are the future—I prefer <a href="https://remix.run/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">Remix</a> or <a href="https://reactrouter.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">React Router</a>.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-foreground">The Engine</h3>
                    <p class="font-serif text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                        In the backend, I use <a href="https://nodejs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">NodeJS</a>.
                        Lately, I've been using and liking <a href="https://deno.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:opacity-80 underline decoration-primary/30">Deno</a>. Since most of the things I build are side projects, I look for services where I can host them for free.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>
                This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4">Astro</a> and <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4">TailwindCSS</a>.
                I use <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4">GitHub</a> for version control and <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4">GitHub Pages</a> for hosting.
            </p>

            <footer class="mt-16 text-center border-t border-border pt-12">
                <p class="text-lg italic text-muted-foreground mb-4">Finding me elsewhere</p>
                <a
                    href="https://mastodon.social/@giwan"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity"
                >
                    mastodon.social/@giwan
                </a>
            </footer>
        </div>
    </div>
</PageLayout>
